  "prompt": "Can someone screenshot a snap after I block them?",
  "response": "Once you block someone on Snapchat, they will no longer be able to see your Snapchat profile, send you messages, or view your stories. However, if they previously had access to your content and took screenshots before you blocked them, they would still have those screenshots. After blocking, they won't have the ability to capture new screenshots of your content, since they won't be able to access it. Nonetheless, always exercise caution with what you share online, as digital information can sometimes be captured or shared in ways that are beyond your control.",
